#Approach:

Rearrange Array Elements by Sign – Two Pointer Approach

Is problem me equal number of positive aur negative numbers diye hote hain
aur hume array ko is tarah arrange karna hota hai ki positive aur negative alternate aaye
aur order bhi same rahe (relative order maintain karna hai).

Hum ek naya array banate hain aur do pointers use karte hain:
pIdx = 0 → positive numbers ke liye (even index)
nIdx = 1 → negative numbers ke liye (odd index)

Array traverse karte hain:
Agar element positive hai to usse ans[pIdx] par daal do aur pIdx += 2
Agar element negative hai to usse ans[nIdx] par daal do aur nIdx += 2

Isse positive even index par aur negative odd index par aayenge
aur alternating pattern ban jayega.

Important:
Yeh approach tab use hoti hai jab positive aur negative numbers equal ho.

Agar positive aur negative numbers unequal ho,
to pehle saare positive aur negative numbers alag arrays me store karo,
phir merge sort ki tarah alternate karke final array banao,
aur jo elements bach jaye unhe end me add kar do.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:
class Solution {
    public int[] rearrangeArray(int[] nums) {

        int n = nums.length;
        int[] ans = new int[n];
        int pIdx = 0;        
        int nIdx = 1;

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            if(nums[i] < 0){
                ans[nIdx] = nums[i];
                nIdx += 2;
            }
            else{
                ans[pIdx] = nums[i];
                pIdx += 2;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
